results.name: Array read by antidiagonals: T(n,k) is the number of 3-connected triangulations of a disk up to orientation-preserving isomorphisms with n interior nodes and k nodes on the boundary, n >= 1, k >= 3.
comment: The initial terms of this sequence can also be computed using the tool "plantri", in particular the command "./plantri -u -v -o -P [n]" will compute values for a diagonal.
